<item>
            <title>[KAFKA-3299] KafkaConnect: DistributedHerder shouldn&apos;t wait forever to read configs after rebalance</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-3299</link>
                <project id="12311720" key="KAFKA">Kafka</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Right now, the handleRebalance code calls readConfigToEnd with timeout of MAX_INT if it isn&apos;t the leader.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The normal workerSyncTimeoutMs is probably sufficient.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;At least this allows a worker to time-out, get back to the tick() loop and check the &quot;stopping&quot; flag to see if it should shut down, to prevent it from hanging forever.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It doesn&apos;t resolve the question of what we should do with a worker that repeatedly fails to read configuration.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
